0Z","msg":"應該香港台灣都睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d64d4444519f42eee8786944685ecc03ac4775b4","tid":1823013,"uid":36722,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"382628d3edb1f423c657cb4815ee6ebd098808f7","tid":1823013,"uid":210351,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T08:25:27.000Z","msg":"應該香港台灣都睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T08:56:32.000Z","msg":"台灣封左關點睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/itdog1.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"88c76e8d000eaf2ca64ea4076a1c50bc328d8e37","tid":1823013,"uid":197098,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T11:35:45.000Z","msg":"I saw them live at Saitama Super Arena twice with my friends last year which were absolutely incredible and unforgettable. I remember the first time we saw their concert we were late. I said &quot;look at the time. The concert will have begun.&quot; It was quarter after eight. The concert would've started by then. They've been strutting their stuff since they were children so don't sell them short. At the end of the last encore they bowed onstage soaking up the applause. They met with a standing ovation and thunderous applause. The band and the dancers and acrobats who were invited to perform alongside them gave a superb performance. The choreography, the lighting and stage design and the glow sticks were magnificent and exceeded our expectations. My cousin is planning on having the band endorse his company's products but he'll have to make it financially worthwhile for them. My cousin is very career-oriented. So do the band. They have a worthwhile career and job as I consider music performing a worthwhile career. On top of being an incredible singer, the lead singer is an avid runner. He took part in a three thousand metre race where he came second. He rose to the challenge of passing the runners who were ahead of him earlier, ran for all he was worth and dived over the finish line. His family and lots of his friends and fans congratulated him on having won the race as he held the trophy up. The race was the opportunity for all the worlds best male runners to strut their stuff. It was truly memorable. After the second concert we saw we dined in a nearby ramen restaurant. I remember the table was sticky maybe because the staff forgot to wipe it up so I asked them to wipe it up. Later I spilt a bowl of miso soup all over the table and my trousers sobi had to wipe the spilled soup up. We had a friendly chat with a lady sitting at a nearby table who told us once upon a time a whole village in tokyo was wiped out by a catastrophic earthquake which was fascinating to hear. When I finished my bowl of ramen I wiped my mouth on my sleeve lol and a few pieces of tissue. The next day we had supper at an italian restaurant nearby originally but we realised we didn't like the menu. As we were leaving a waiter came up to us so I said &quot;thank you but we've changed our minds&quot; A stout man and a svelte girl also found out they didn't like the menu so they said &quot;thank you. We're in the mood for a different cuisine tonight. We'll be back another time. Thank you for your hospitality.&quot; There's an exquisite cafe nearby of which the interior and the exterior are artistically and exquisitely designed. The other day my friend Joe spilt his cappuccino all over his work and down his tie so he ended up wiping up this mess lol. I enjoy drinking coffee and chatting with the baristas there so much that I occasionally make it worth the baristas' while. Yesterday I assigned five hours for practising the band's songs on my piccolo, flute, oboe, cor anglais (english horn), clarinet, E-flat clarinet, bass clarinet, bassoon, contrabassoon, harp and saxophone. I practised with my friends who played triangle, tsmboitine, castanets, cymbals (hi-hat, clash and ride), sleigh bells (jingle bells), gongs, bass drum and snare drum, all of which have indefinite pitch. Adding these instruments makes the music more rhythmic. Sax, cor anglais and clarinet are transposing instruments. Saxophone, clarinet and bass clarinet are single reed instruments whereas oboe, cor anglais bassoon and contrabassoon are double reed instruments. Flute is a reedless instrument."},{"pid":"ced485eff4c3bb257af0835b84deea467dfac9f9","tid":1823013,"uid":210351,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"d64d4444519f42eee8786944685ecc03ac4775b4","tid":1823013,"uid":36722,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"382628d3edb1f423c657cb4815ee6ebd098808f7","tid":1823013,"uid":210351,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T08:25:27.000Z","msg":"應該香港台灣都睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T08:56:32.000Z","msg":"台灣封左關點睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/itdog1.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T17:32:35.000Z","msg":"信佢到時有得去"},{"pid":"e20d7ea9f33cb72880a608b89e70fb55dec5533c","tid":1823013,"uid":9425,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"ced485eff4c3bb257af0835b84deea467dfac9f9","tid":1823013,"uid":210351,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"d64d4444519f42eee8786944685ecc03ac4775b4","tid":1823013,"uid":36722,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"382628d3edb1f423c657cb4815ee6ebd098808f7","tid":1823013,"uid":210351,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T08:25:27.000Z","msg":"應該香港台灣都睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-17T08:56:32.000Z","msg":"台灣封左關點睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/itdog1.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime